Pairwise products: (-1)(-2) + (-1)(-3) + (-2)(-3) = 2 + 3 + 6 = 11. Therefore, b = 11. So, (a, b) = (6, 11). 2. Multiset {-1, 1, 6}: Sum: (-1) + 1 + 6 = 6. Therefore, a = -6. Pairwise products: (-1)(1) + (-1)(6) + (1)(6) = -1 -6 + 6 = -1. Therefore, b = -1. So, (a, b) = (-6, -1). 3. Multiset {-1, 2, 3}: Sum: (-1) + 2 + 3 = 4. Therefore, a = -4. Pairwise products: (-1)(2) + (-1)(3) + (2)(3) = -2 -3 +6 = 1. Therefore, b = 1. So, (a, b) = (-4, 1). 4. Multiset {-2, 1, 3}: Sum: (-2) + 1 + 3 = 2. Therefore, a = -2.
